# ONL046 Sync Error: Feature Not Included in QuickBooks Online Subscription

If you see the error:

**“ONL046 Sync Error: Feature not included in QuickBooks Online subscription. Please upgrade QuickBooks version.”**

this means your QuickBooks Online subscription does not support one or more features selected in your Expensify export settings.

Until the subscription includes the required feature, syncing or exporting will fail.

---

## Why ONL046 Happens

Each QuickBooks Online plan supports different accounting features.

If your Expensify Workspace is configured to use a feature that your QuickBooks Online subscription does not include, QuickBooks blocks the sync and returns error **ONL046**.

Note: **QuickBooks Self-Employed is not supported** with Expensify.

---

## How to Fix ONL046

1. Log in to QuickBooks Online.
2. Confirm which subscription plan you are using.
3. Review the feature support table below.
4. Either:
   - Upgrade your QuickBooks Online subscription, or  
   - Adjust your Expensify export settings to use supported features only.

---

## QuickBooks Online Feature Support by Plan

| Feature                         | Simple Start | Essentials | Plus |
|----------------------------------|--------------|------------|------|
| GL Accounts as Categories        | Yes          | Yes        | Yes  |
| Classes                          | No           | No         | Yes  |
| Locations                        | No           | No         | Yes  |
| Customers                        | No           | No         | Yes  |
| Projects                         | No           | No         | Yes  |
| Vendor Bills                     | No           | Yes        | Yes  |
| Expense Reports                  | Yes          | Yes        | Yes  |
| Journal Entries                  | Yes          | Yes        | Yes  |
| Credit Card Transaction          | Yes          | Yes        | Yes  |
| Debit Card Transaction           | Yes          | Yes        | Yes  |
| Tax                              | Yes          | Yes        | Yes  |
| Billable                         | No           | No         | Yes  |

If you are using features such as **Classes**, **Locations**, **Projects**, or **Billable**, you must be on the **QuickBooks Online Plus** plan.

---

## How to Adjust Expensify Export Settings

If you do not want to upgrade your QuickBooks Online subscription:

1. Go to the navigation tabs on the left.
2. Click **Settings**.
3. Click **Workspaces**.
4. Select your Workspace.
5. Click **Accounting**.
6. Update export settings to remove unsupported features.

After making changes, click **Sync Now** to test the connection again.

---

# FAQ

## Does ONL046 mean the QuickBooks connection is broken?

No. The connection is active, but your subscription does not support a selected feature.

---

## Can I use QuickBooks Self-Employed with Expensify?

No. QuickBooks Self-Employed is not supported.

---

## Do I need to reconnect QuickBooks Online?

No. You only need to upgrade your QuickBooks Online subscription or adjust your export settings to use supported features.
